<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb6d22819-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300ii–4"><num value="300ii–4">§ 300ii–4.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subchapter, $10,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2026 through 2030.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb6d2281a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title XXIX, § 2905, as added <ref href="/us/pl/109/442/s2">Pub. L. 109–442, § 2</ref>, <date date="2006-12-21">Dec. 21, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/3296">120 Stat. 3296</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/116/324/s2/b">Pub. L. 116–324, § 2(b)</ref>, <date date="2021-01-05">Jan. 5, 2021</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/5085">134 Stat. 5085</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/119/75/dJ/tV/s6506/b">Pub. L. 119–75, div. J, title V, § 6506(b)</ref>, <date date="2026-02-03">Feb. 3, 2026</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/140/693">140 Stat. 693</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb6d2281b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
